webLinks.linkText: Club Championships Triathlon - road closure notification

properties.headline: Triathlon - Saturday 14 November - FORSTER various roads incl Beach St, Strand St and Underwood Rd approaching Main Beach
properties.otherAdvice:
The Club Championships Triathlon will take place on Saturday around Main Beach in Forster from 6am until 10:30am.

Local roads in the area will be closed for the event from 6am until 9:30am including sections of Beach St, North St, Oyster Pde, Head St, Hadley St, Lincoln St, Boundary St, Strand St, Underwood Rd, Cliff Rd and Burgess Rd.

Detours will be in place via Head St, Macintosh St and The Lakes Way. Access will be maintained for residents the during closures.

There will also be restricted access for Lakeview Cres, Karloo St, Hesper Dr and Southern Pkwy from 6am until 9:30am. 

Forster Bridge pedestrian pathway will be used for the event and will not be accessible from 7am to 8:30am. During that time a shuttle bus will be provided for non event participants to transport them from one side of the bridge to the other.

Motorists in the area advised to allow extra time.

roads.mainStreet: various roads incl Beach St, Strand St and Underwood Rd

properties.headline: Rugby League tournament - Saturday 14 November - GOSFORD Dane Dr between Central Coast Hwy AND Donnison St
properties.otherAdvice:
The National Indigenous Rugby League Tribal League 2020 tournament will be taking place on Saturday at Central Coast Stadium from 9:30am until 6:30pm approx. 

Traffic may be heavier than usual on roads approaching the stadium including Central Coast Hwy, Pacific Hwy, Brisbane Water Dr, Donnison St and Mann St as attendees travel to and from the event.

Motorists should allow extra travel time and be aware of increased pedestrian activity on roads in the area.

properties.headline: Triathlon - Saturday 21 November - PORT STEPHENS Gan Gan Rd at Frost Rd
properties.otherAdvice:
The Port Stephens Triathlon is taking place at One Mile Beach on Saturday from 5:30am to 2:30pm. 

Road closures will be in place for the event from 6am until 1pm on sections of Gan Gan Rd, Frost Rd, Hannah Pde, Eucalyptus Dr, Melaleuca Dr and Casuarina Cl. Resident access will be maintained during the closures. 

Vehicle access to Gan Gan Rd and Frost Rd will be managed by traffic controllers when there are safe breaks between cyclists. Motorists can access the area from Gan Gan Rd at Anna Bay. 

Nelson Bay Rd may be busier than usual. Motorists should allow extra travel time and follow the directions of traffic controllers.

properties.headline: Cricket - Friday 27 November - MOORE PARK Moore Park Rd, Anzac Pde, Lang Rd, Eastern Distributor approaching The Sydney Cricket Ground

arrangementAttachments.displayName: Moore Park walking & transport route map
arrangementAttachments.linkName: Moore Park walking & transport route map

properties.otherAdvice:
First One Day International: Australia v India at The SCG from 2:40pm until 10:10pm approx.

Traffic is expected to be heavier than usual on Anzac Pde, Eastern Distributor, Moore Park Rd, Cleveland St and Lang Rd approaching Moore Park as cricket fans travel to the match on Friday afternoon. 

Driver Ave will be partially closed from 11:30am and will reopen once crowds have safely cleared the precinct. 

Special event clearways are in effect on various roads around Moore Park from 12pm midday until 12am midnight including sections of Moore Park Rd, Albion St, Lang Rd, Chalmers St, Fitzroy St, Flinders St and Foveaux St.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.
